.TH XIL\-SFX\-LIB "1" "2026\-04\-24" "xil\-pipeline 0.1.8" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xil\-sfx\-lib
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xil\-sfx\-lib
[-h] [--api | --local] [--sfx-dir DIR] [--search TEXT] [--all] [--verbose] [--json] [--export-kit [DIR]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Discover personally generated Sound Effects from the ElevenLabs account or local SFX/ directory

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-api\fR
Query ElevenLabs /v1/sound\-generation/history (requires sound_generation
permission)

.TP
\fB\-\-local\fR
Scan local SFX/ directory only (no API key needed)

.TP
\fB\-\-sfx\-dir\fR \fI\,DIR\/\fR
Local SFX directory to scan (default: SFX/)

.TP
\fB\-\-search\fR \fI\,TEXT\/\fR
Case\-insensitive substring filter on the prompt/filename

.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
(API mode) Paginate through the full account history; default: most recent 100

.TP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR, \fB\-v\fR
Print all fields for each record

.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Output results as a JSON array

.TP
\fB\-\-export\-kit\fR \fI\,[DIR]\/\fR
Export SFX inventory JSON + scriptwriter reference doc to DIR (default:
current directory)

